ru.ifmo.ctddev.filippov.implementor

Class Implementor

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.ifmo.ctddev.filippov.implementor.Implementor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Impler, JarImpler

    public class Implementor
extends Object
implements JarImpler
    This class shows implementation of JarImpler interface

    It can generate implementation (java file) for interfaces and classes that can be implemented/extended Class implements all methods that should be overridden, their default return value gets out according to javadoc primitive types (see Primitive Data Types). Implemented class name is equal to class name that we must implement plus "Impl" suffix

    It can also generate jar archive with that certain class.

    If something went wrong while creating java or jar files and it is impossible to generate such file, than ImplerException is thrown with error message

    See Also:
    Impler, JarImpler, ImplerException

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar(Class<?> token,
                         File jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        This method creates jar file with name jarFile in root directory. .jar file is obtained by compiling imlementation of token class by calling implement(java.lang.Class<?>, java.io.File) function (so, implemented java class also creates). Throws ImplerException if something went wrong and jar file cannot be created
        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:

        jarFile - target jar file.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if something went wrong, ImplerException throws
        See Also:
